DnaJ Binds to Histidine-Tagged oa2 Independent of ATP The behavior of DnaJ in the ATP elution experiment, shown in Figure 4, was surprising. In sharp contrast to DnaK and GrpE, DnaJ was not eluted from the Ni2+column upon addition of ATP but instead was eluted together with @-C-his by the subsequent 30-150 mM imidazole gradient (Figure 4D; fractions 27-34). This surprising result indicates that DnaJ itself, in the absence of DnaK and GrpE and independent of ATP, can efficiently and stably bind to 032-C-his.
